ed\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span></div>				</div>\n			</div>\n			<p class=\"reviewer\">\n				Di <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/makintracks/\"><img alt=\'\' src=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/859e6a6c6b30609cfa3601b80994c962?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g\' srcset=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/859e6a6c6b30609cfa3601b80994c962?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x\' class=\'avatar avatar-16 photo\' height=\'16\' width=\'16\' loading=\'lazy\' decoding=\'async\'/></a><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/makintracks/\" class=\"reviewer-name\">makintracks</a> il <span class=\"review-date\">Giugno 24, 2024</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class=\"review-body\"><!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>My first time asking Woo for help and I am so impressed with the assistance I received. Thank you very much for clarifying the issue with the nofollow tags on buttons. It is a relief knowing I have nothing to worry about.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"review\">\n	<div class=\"review-head\">\n		<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n			<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n				<h4 class=\"review-title\">Great support</h4>\n				<div class=\"star-rating\">\n				<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"5 su 5 stelle\" data-title-template=\"%s su 5 stelle\" data-rating=\"5\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span></div>				</div>\n			</div>\n			<p class=\"reviewer\">\n				Di <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/42krunning/\"><img alt=\'\' src=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/88ef4102c993276bc7dba77c6e34fe9a?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g\' srcset=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/88ef4102c993276bc7dba77c6e34fe9a?s=32&#